Depends: ${misc:Depends}, bash (>= 4.0), jq
Recommends: wmctrl, xdotool
Description: Save and restore window layouts across Linux desktop environments
 Saveland is a utility for capturing and restoring window positions,
 sizes, and workspace information across different desktop environments.
 .
 It allows users to save their desktop setup and recreate it later with
 a single command. Currently supports Hyprland and GNOME (X11) environments.
 .
 Features:
  * Save window layouts across multiple workspaces
  * Restore applications with their original size and position
  * Support for multiple instances of the same application
  * Automatic desktop environment detection